We recommended that the:

Municipal Health Officer and Public School District Supervisor (i) submit a certification that all the drugs and medicines requested and procured in CY 2020 fall within and conform with the current edition of the PNF; otherwise, submit a detailed list of those that did not conform, as the case may be; and (ii) henceforth; observe strict compliance with Section 2 of EO No. 49 whenever drugs and medicines are requisitioned for procurement;

Acting Municipal Treasurer submit the official receipt issued by Thea Miel Pharma Plus amounting to ₱184,435.78, accompanied by a written explanation on why it was not submitted previously;

Municipal Accountant henceforth, ensure that all purchases of drugs and medicines are thoroughly reviewed as to completeness of supporting documents as part of her internal audit services pursuant to Section 474.b(5) of RA No. 7160; and

Municipal Mayor impose strict adherence to the instructions on the use of transaction forms prescribed under the GAM for LGUs, Volume II, with emphasis on the application of control numbers and indication of date on the Acceptance and Inspection Report.

We recommended that the:

Municipal Inventory Committee conduct a complete physical count of PPE, including the roads and other road network components, in accordance with Section 124 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume I, and prepare the Report on Physical Count of the Road Network System using the format provided under Annex “C” of COA Circular No. 2015-008;

Municipal Engineer prepare the Report on Local Road Network using the format provided under Annex “A” of COA Circular No. 2015-008 and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer, copy furnished the Audit Team;

Municipal Treasurer, as the Property Officer, prepare and maintain the Road Network Property Cards for all roads and its components, using the format provided under Annex “E” of COA Circular No. 2015-008;

Municipal Accountant (i) prepare a reconciliation of the Report on Physical Count of the Road Network System submitted by the Inventory Committee and the Report on Local Road Network submitted by the Municipal Engineer; (ii) prepare the journal entry voucher to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Network Ledger Card, respectively; and (iii) henceforth, ensure adequate disclosure of information regarding the Local Road Network on the Notes to the Financial Statements as prescribed under Annex “B” of COA Circular No. 2015-008; and

Municipal Mayor (i) cause the creation of a plantilla position for the General Services Officer, subject to availability of funds; (ii) through the Human Resource Management Officer, initiate the search for qualified applicants for the said position; and (iii) enjoin the concerned department heads to comply with all the requirements of COA Circular No. 2015-008.

We recommended that the:

Former OIC-Municipal Engineer and the MPDC submit justification for signing the recommendation on the certificates of inspection and completion despite lack of inspection report, STE, and As-Built Plan;

Municipal Engineer prepare a verified computation of liquidated damages for the road project for approval of the Municipal Mayor;

Municipal Mayor issue a demand letter to the contractor requiring payment of liquidated damages, duly supported by the computation prepared by the Municipal Engineer; and

Municipal Accountant henceforth, make sure that no payment for final billing or release of retention money shall be processed and approved without an inspection report duly validated by the authorized project engineer, STE, As-Built Plan and duly approved computation of liquidated damages.

