Municipal Mayor impose strict adherence to the instructions on the use of transaction forms prescribed under the GAM for LGUs, Volume II, with emphasis on the application of control numbers and indication of issuance date on the Acceptance and Inspection Report.

We recommended that the:
Acting Municipal Treasurer submit promptly the disbursement vouchers and reports to the Municipal Accountant so that all taxes withheld during the month are included in the Monthly Alphalist of Payees and remitted to the BIR;
Municipal Accountant and the Acting Municipal Treasurer, (i) cause the immediate remittance of all taxes withheld to the BIR to avoid possible interest, penalties and surcharges for late remittances, otherwise they shall be personally liable for the surcharge and interest that may be imposed; and (ii) henceforth, ensure that taxes withheld on contractors and suppliers and compensation of Municipal officials and employees are remitted intact within the prescribed period pursuant to BIR Revenue Regulation No. 2-98 dated April 17, 1998, as amended.

We recommended that the:

Municipal Engineer (i) require the contractor to submit substantial proof that the time extension requests dated January 14 and May 6, 2019 are valid in accordance with Section 10, Annex “E” of the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and that the reasons provided thereon are not due to their fault or negligence; (ii) upon careful evaluation of the validity of time extensions, prepare an updated computation of liquidated damages to be imposed to the contractor and furnish a copy to the Municipal Mayor and the Municipal Accountant; (iii) prepare a written report on the acts or causes which may constitute grounds for termination of contract for the Maringian-Tucadan and Pawa Water System Projects, with all relevant evidence attached including the latest Inspection Report and Statement of Time Elapsed; and (iv) based on the report, recommend to the Head of the Procuring Entity (HOPE) on whether or not to terminate the contracts, take-over the project and forfeit the contractor’s performance security;

Municipal Accountant ensure that liquidated damages as determined by the Municipal Engineer are deducted from any subsequent payment to the contractor;

Municipal Mayor as the HOPE (i) create a Contract Termination Review Committee (CTRC) to assist him on the issuance of Notice to Terminate, evaluation of response to the show cause order, and deciding whether or not to terminate the contracts pursuant to Section V, Annex “I” of the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184, and (ii) depending on the report and recommendation of the CTRC, initiate the contract termination, take-over of the projects and forfeiture of the contractor’s performance security, if warranted; and

Municipal Vice-Mayor/Former Municipal Mayor submit a satisfactory explanation on the basis relied upon in the approval of requests for time suspension/extension dated January 14 and May 6, 2019.

